# Flight Route Evaluator

Read before any work:

1. **SPEC.md** — immutable requirements (do not change during implementation)
2. **IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md** — execution rules and quality gates
3. **TASKS.yaml** — task board; update status as you work
4. **REVIEWER.md** — use when acting as reviewer agent (review only, no implementation)

## Dual-agent workflow

**Coder (Agent mode):** SPEC + IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN + TASKS → write code → stop at gate  
**Reviewer (separate chat):** REVIEWER.md + **git diff** → full review report → APPROVED / CHANGES_REQUESTED → **no fixes**  
**Single-agent MVP:** use IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN § Single-agent MVP start prompt — full self-review report required; only literal APPROVED proceeds

Full prompts: IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md § Agent prompts

After each stage: coder stops at Review Gate; Stage N+1 starts only after reviewer **APPROVED**.

## Execution

- Follow task dependencies in TASKS.yaml
- **Keep TASKS.yaml up to date** — mark each task `in_progress` / `done` / `blocked` as you go; include `notes`, `tests`, `completed_at` when done (see IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN Status tracking rule)
- Mark one task `in_progress` at a time
- Do not implement code unless implementing a task from TASKS.yaml
- Stop after stage gate reports **ready for review** until reviewer **APPROVED**
- **Stage 4** — do not implement unless explicitly requested after MVP

## Non-negotiable constraints

- **Config-driven only** — predefined branches from YAML; no arbitrary search
- **One-stop / single-transfer only**
- **No database** — filesystem cache only
- **No SQL** for flight queries
- **Static bilingual report.html** required; no HTTP server
- **--provider mock** must work without API keys
- **Currency** — show original; score normalized; never silently mix
- **Timezones** — airport-local; late arrival in Asia/Kathmandu
- **Reason codes** — unified taxonomy for failures
- **No provider historical price APIs** — local JSONL accumulation only (Stage 4)
- **JSONL price history allowed** — `history/prices.jsonl` is not a database
- **SU** — warn/unavailable when needed; not a global requirement
- **SupportedAirlines** — advisory; partial/unknown providers not auto-rejected

## Testing

- Unit + integration + golden tests required
- ≥70% coverage on internal/
- No real API tests in CI; no browser automation

Do not add features in SPEC "Do-Not-Implement List" or IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN "Forbidden behaviors".
